article.headline: San Francisco 87, Sonoma State 73
article.story: SAN FRANCISCO (AP) -- Antonio Kellogg scored 22 points in his San Francisco debut and Alan Wiggins added 10 points and 12 rebounds to leading the Dons to an 87-73 win over Division II Sonoma State on Saturday night. Armondo Surratt also had 20 points and five assists for San Francisco, which had just eight players in uniform against Sonoma. University of San Francisco officials said on Friday that men's basketball players were among 13 athletes who would miss time for making nonessential purchases with their scholarship money at the school bookstore. San Francisco coach Jessie Evans said Saturday that junior forward Vince Polakovic, sophomore forward Jesse Byrd and sophomore center James Morgan would miss three games as a result of the infractions. But the Dons, who started two freshmen and two sophomores, still shot 61.5 percent in the first half, with five of its eight players reaching double figures. Sonoma State, ranked No. 15 in an NCAA preseason Division II poll, trailed by as many as 19 points in the second half and committed 22 turnovers.
